The paper discusses the use of memcapacitive devices in computing, which falls under the category of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET). The paper also discusses the use of memcapacitive devices in logic gates and crossbar classifiers, which are related to Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Architecture (cs.AR). The fabrication process of the devices involves metal-oxide materials, which is related to Electromagnetics (cs.EM) and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE).
